  + [purpose] is map finite explicit-formula residual stability across x ranges, zero-pair cutoff counts, and sharp/Fejer/Lanczos/Hann window policies before attempting another explicit/Euler bridge
  + [not_purpose] is proof, disproof, RH evidence, zero certification, critical-line authority, universal smoothing-window ranking, or bridge identity

  = must: use exact finite psi(x), theta(x), and pi(x) rows for sampled x
  = must: compare at least seven x samples and at least five zero-pair cutoff counts
  = must: compare sharp, Fejer, Lanczos, and Hann windows
  = must: report best window by x and zero-pair count
  = must: report window win counts and average residual magnitude across the bounded grid
  = must: report cutoff transitions by x and window so instability remains visible
  = must: mark output proof_status as finite_explicit_residual_stability_atlas_not_zero_certification
  = must: treat mpmath zetazero as numerical library lookup, not proof authority
  - never: infer RH proof, disproof, zero certification, or critical-line truth from finite residual stability
  - never: collapse local minima into identity
  - never: fuse explicit-formula residual rails with Euler-product/log-derivative rails without a later source-defined shared comparison unit

